# 🎵 Hand Gesture Music Controller (MediaPipe + OpenCV + pycaw + comtypes )

# ONLY COMPATIBLE FOR Windows ! BUT WITH MINOR CHANGES YOU CAN MAKE IT FOR MACOS ALSO ⚠️⚠️

Built using:
- [MediaPipe] for hand tracking
- [OpenCV] for camera and UI
- [osascript / AppleScript] for macOS system volume and media key control

> ✅ Now compatible with **macOS** (Apple Silicon & Intel).
>  requires pycaw or comtypes (Windows-only).

## ✋ Supported Gestures

| Gesture                | Action            |
|------------------------|-------------------|
| All fingers down       | Play/Pause        |
| Only index finger up   | Next Song         |
| Index + Middle up      | Previous Song     |
| Only thumb up          | Volume Up         |
| Only pinky up          | Volume Down       |


## 🛠️ Setup

### 1. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install opencv-python mediapipe ...

In windows / linux - requirements installation is compulsory .

### 2. Grant Permissions 

macOS requires you to give your Terminal (or IDE) access to:
- **Camera**: System Settings → Privacy & Security → Camera → enable Terminal/VS Code
- **Accessibility** (for media key control): System Settings → Privacy & Security → Accessibility → enable Terminal/VS Code

### 3. Run

```bash
python gesture.py
```
